description:
&lt;p&gt;Tees Esk and Wear Valleys NHS Foundation Trust is committed to supporting the health and wellbeing of its employees. The Trust Employee Psychology Service provides support to help employees recover from, and develop resilience to, work-related stress and associated anxiety/depression.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Principal Clinical Psychologist to work within the Employee Psychology Service. The role is Trustwide and will involve direct therapeutic activities, clinical supervision of 8a clinicians, overseeing various service development projects, liaison and co-working with the Employee Support Service and working with various teams across the Trust to support their mental well-being.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be HPCC registered and have experience of providing a range of psychological interventions for trauma, anxiety and depression etc, and will report directly to the Head/Consultant Clinical Psychologist for the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr Barry Speak, Consultant Clinical Psychologist. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Email: barry.speak@nhs.net. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tel: 01642 451796.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
